The paper deals with the problem of personalized pricing algorithms and how consumers can protect themselves against them. This problem falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) as it involves strategic decision making by both the seller and the consumer. The paper also uses computational methods to develop an algorithm for the consumer, which falls under the categories of computational engineering, finance, and artificial intelligence (cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses optimal stopping time theory, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
